  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "expat security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for expat is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "expat is a stream-oriented XML parser library written in C. expat excels with files too large to fit RAM, and where performance and flexibility are crucial.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nlibexpat before 2.8.2 has an integer overflow in storeAtts.(CVE-2026-56403)\n\nlibexpat before 2.8.2 has an integer overflow in addBinding.(CVE-2026-56404)\n\nlibexpat before 2.8.2 has an integer overflow in getAttributeId.(CVE-2026-56405)\n\nlibexpat before 2.8.2 has an integer overflow in XML_ParseBuffer because it lacked a check that was present in XML_Parse.(CVE-2026-56406)\n\nlibexpat before 2.8.2 has an integer overflow in doProlog that is related to storeEntityValue and entity textLen.(CVE-2026-56407)\n\nlibexpat before 2.8.2 has an integer overflow in copyString.(CVE-2026-56408)\n\nxmlwf in libexpat before 2.8.2 has an integer overflow for the output filename when -d outputDir is used.(CVE-2026-56409)\n\nxmlwf in libexpat before 2.8.2 has an integer overflow in resolveSystemId.(CVE-2026-56410)\n\nxmlwf in libexpat before 2.8.2 has an integer overflow in endDoctypeDecl via NOTATION declarations.(CVE-2026-56411)\n\nlibexpat before 2.8.2 does not consider XML_TOK_DATA_CHARS in doCdataSection and thus lacks handler call depth tracking for various calls from within handlers in cases of a policy violation. Thus, a use-after-free can occur. NOTE: this issue exists because of an incomplete fix for CVE-2026-50219.(CVE-2026-56412)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for expat is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of medium. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Medium",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "expat",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
